But in both cases, the result will be `F(b) - F(a)` regardless of whether `a ≤ b` or not.

So for `f(x) = 1 / x`, the antiderivative is `log x` (since `x > 0`), and the integral becomes `log b - log a`.

Similarly, for `g(x) = 1 / x²`, the antiderivative is `-1 / x`, and the integral becomes `-1 / b - (-1 / a) = 1 / a - 1 / b`.

